cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on semantic textual similarity tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel representation for text and a non-parametric similarity measure, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also discusses similarities between word vectors, which is related to information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a method that outperforms current baselines, which is related to performance evaluation and could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
